    <!-- EXECUTIVE SUMMARY -->
    <section class="section" id="executive">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">01</span>
        <h2>Executive Summary</h2>
      </div>

      <p>MoveEasy is a well-conceived and technically ambitious platform. The shared infrastructure model — single KYC, unified wallet, central AI brain — is the right architectural bet for a multi-product fintech. The codebase shows genuine engineering effort: async-first payment processing via BullMQ, HMAC-signed vouchers with geo-lock validation, proper ACID transactions, and a Claude-powered orchestrator that is meaningfully integrated (not bolted on).</p>

      <p>However, <strong>the build is not production-safe in its current state</strong>. Four security issues are critical blockers for live payment processing. The most severe is the absence of Ozow webhook signature verification, which would allow an attacker to fraudulently confirm EFT payments without ever sending money. Three financial logic bugs would result in real monetary losses under normal usage. Several FICA/AML compliance gaps need closing before FSCA scrutiny.</p>

      <div class="callout">
        <div class="callout-label">Verdict</div>
        <h3>Strong foundation — fix security and financial bugs before going live</h3>
        <p>The core architecture patterns are correct and deployable. The 4 critical items below are straightforward fixes. Resolve those, address the 3 financial logic bugs, and this platform can proceed to controlled launch.</p>
      </div>

      <h3>What's Working Well</h3>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li class="check-pass">Async-first payment processing — BullMQ workers handle all fund movements, HTTP requests never touch money directly</li>
        <li class="check-pass">ACID transactions with <code>withTransaction()</code> wrapper used consistently across financial operations</li>
        <li class="check-pass">HMAC-signed fuel vouchers with proper 4-hour TTL expiry</li>
        <li class="check-pass">Geo-lock enforcement using Haversine distance (500m radius) — correct mathematical implementation</li>
        <li class="check-pass">KYC gate (<code>requireKYC()</code> middleware) applied before all sensitive routes with tier-level granularity</li>
        <li class="check-pass">Idempotency key handling on SafeBet deposits prevents duplicate processing</li>
        <li class="check-pass">AI Brain properly scoped — multi-turn context, structured JSON outputs, financial health narratives</li>
        <li class="check-pass">Database schema: BIGINT cents throughout, no floating-point money</li>
        <li class="check-pass">Nginx config: TLS 1.2/1.3 only, HSTS, security headers, rate limiting per route</li>
        <li class="check-pass">PCI-DSS: no raw card data stored — tokenisation delegated to gateways</li>
        <li class="check-pass">Compliance flags table and AML pattern detection defined in Brain orchestrator</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- ARCHITECTURE -->
    <section class="section" id="architecture">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-number">02</span>
        <h2>Architecture Assessment</h2>
      </div>

      <p>The overall architecture is sound. The dual-layer API design (Hono at edge on Cloudflare Workers + Express on EC2) is a sensible pattern for latency-sensitive auth/routing separated from business logic. The shared infrastructure model correctly treats KYC, wallet, and payment rails as platform primitives that all products consume.</p>

      <div class="finding good">
        <span class="finding-badge badge-good">Good</span>
        <div class="finding-title">Async Payment Doctrine</div>
        <p>The codebase consistently follows the <em>"payments MUST be async"</em> doctrine. HTTP handlers create records and queue jobs; all fund movements happen in BullMQ workers with retry logic (<code>attempts: 3, backoff: exponential</code>). This is correct for a fintech platform and prevents partial-state failures from network timeouts.</p>
        <div class="finding-file">worker.js · safebet.js · webhooks.js</div>
      </div>

      <div class="finding warning">
        <span class="finding-badge badge-warning">Warning</span>
        <div class="finding-title">Dual Codebase: Express vs Hono — Sync Not Enforced</div>
