      <div class="finding warning">
        <span class="finding-badge badge-warning">Gap — COMP-01</span>
        <div class="finding-title">No SAR Filing Workflow</div>
        <p>The <code>compliance_flags</code> table has a <code>sar_filed</code> boolean, and the Brain correctly identifies AML patterns (structuring, high velocity, geo mismatch). However, there is no implemented route, cron job, or dashboard for compliance officers to review flagged users and file a Suspicious Activity Report with the FIC. The flag creation logic exists; the downstream workflow does not. For FICA compliance, a human-in-the-loop SAR review process must be built before live transactions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="finding warning">
        <span class="finding-badge badge-warning">Gap — COMP-02</span>
        <div class="finding-title">KYC Tier 2 Not Defined in Schema</div>
        <p>The <code>requireKYC(2)</code> gate is used in the FuelFlex apply route (which requires a TransUnion credit check), but the schema's <code>users</code> table has no <code>kyc_tier</code> column in the reviewed version. The auth middleware does reference <code>req.user.kyc_tier</code> suggesting it's in the <code>ecosystem_sync</code> or <code>users</code> table, but the schema <code>CREATE TABLE users</code> shown above doesn't define it. Verify the deployed schema matches the middleware expectations — a mismatch means KYC tier gates silently fail (tier evaluates to <code>undefined</code> which is <code>&lt; 2</code>, correctly blocking, but for the wrong reason).</p>
        <div class="finding-file">backend/src/middleware/auth.js · infra/postgres/schema.sql</div>
      </div>

      <div class="finding warning">
        <span class="finding-badge badge-warning">Gap — COMP-03</span>
        <div class="finding-title">POPIA: AI Brain Receives Non-Redacted User Data</div>
        <p>The AI Brain's <code>analyseUserTelemetry()</code> method passes a <code>UserFinancialProfile</code> and raw telemetry events to Claude. The system prompt mentions <em>"PII redacted from Brain analysis prompts"</em> but the implementation passes <code>user_id</code>, transaction amounts, merchant IDs, and geo data directly. For POPIA compliance, the Brain should receive a pseudonymised profile (hashed user ID, no direct identifiers). Additionally, the Anthropic API call sends this data to a US-based API — verify your Anthropic data processing agreement covers South African POPIA cross-border data transfer requirements.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="finding info">
        <span class="finding-badge badge-info">Note — COMP-04</span>
        <div class="finding-title">SafeBet FSCA Classification Risk</div>
        <p>SafeBet clips a percentage of gambling deposits and converts to USDC, promising yield ("trading gains" at 12-month unlock). This feature profile — collecting client money, promising returns, converting to crypto — may require FSCA registration as a Collective Investment Scheme or Financial Services Provider. The engineering implementation is solid, but the product should be reviewed by a South African financial law specialist before launch to confirm it falls outside CIS/FSP licensing requirements or to obtain the appropriate licence.</p>
